<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4298141>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Fig. 1. Colour variation in the metasoma of Lasioglossum (D.) hudsoniellum (Cockerell, 1919). A. Yellow-orange. B. Red-orange. C. Reddish brown. D. Black. “Red-tailed” Lasioglossum (Dialictus) are considered to be any species with natural colour matching A or B." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4298141/files/figure.png" .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4298227>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Fig. 42. Georeferenced collection records of Lasioglossum (D.) hudsoniellum (Cockerell, 1919) (black squares) and predicted distribution by maximum entropy ecological niche modeling in Maxent (colour shading). Warmer colours indicate higher cloglog probability of occurrence." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4298227/files/figure.png" .

